com.jayway.android.robotium.remotecontrol

Class By

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.jayway.android.robotium.remotecontrol.By
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    By.ClassName, By.CssSelector, By.Id, By.Name, By.TagName, By.Text, By.Xpath

    public abstract class By
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    From release4.0, Robotium begins to support some APIs who use com.jayway.android.robotium.solo.By as
    parameter. To support this kind of APIs, this class was created, it implements interface Serializable
    so that it can be transported as an object thru our TCP protocol.

    In release 5.0.1, Robotium was refactored to use com.robotium.solo package

    Example of usage:
    At controller side, user can simply call xpath(String) etc. to get a By instance 'by'.
    and send this object thru the wire.
    At the device side, we receive that object 'by' and we call toSoloBy()
    to get a Solo's By object, which can be used by Robotium's APIs.

    This class copy the content of com.robotium.solo.By, if that class is modified, we needs
    to update this class also.

    Since:
    May 14, 2013
    Update MAR 17, 2014 to support com.robotium.solo package.
    Author:
    Lei Wang, SAS Institute, Inc
